Well I am not a doctor so I can't give a clear diagnosis but from what you have described I can surely say that you're parents are true  NARCISSISTS they think that they are more important and much more intelligent then others, for them nothing exists but themselves, to them everyone around is inferior and not essential. Your parents want to see their failed selves in you so they want you to succeed which turns out completely the other way around. As to your specific problem, you cant do a lot I can only suggest if you can borrow or somehow get money you can only buy a new cheap phone to make new social media accounts so you can have complete privacy over your conversations but you will have to hide it very well. At the same time search for cameras in your room. Tracking your location is a problem that you cant resolve until you leave your parents completely. If you have a good relationship with your grandparents try moving to their house. You are now 18 so if things turn ugly and your parents hold you against your will and also threaten you, maybe get evidence against them and you can sue them, but I am not a lawyer + I don't live in the USA so idk the legal system there. I am truly sorry for your situation, I was raised in a free environment so I just can't understand how someone can press someone else like that. Sorry but I see you're parents as some kind of true psychopaths that don't understand that their actions are completely wrong and also cause negative consequences to others. I wish you luck and hope that you succeed in leaving your parents.
